'''门户地区'''（{{lang-en|Gateway Region}}）位于美国[[新泽西州|新泽西州]]的东北部，包括[[博根县|博根县]]、[[埃塞克斯县_(新泽西州)|埃塞克斯县]]、[[哈德逊县|哈德逊县]]、[[巴赛克县|巴赛克县]]、[[联合县_(新泽西州)|联合县]]和[[米德尔塞克斯县_(新泽西州)|米德尔塞克斯县]]。它是该州最为城市化的一部分，有400多万人口，并且拥有该州大部分的大城市，最初多是作为[[纽约都会区|纽约都会区]]一部分的郊区而存在<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://query.nytimes.com/mem/archive-free/pdf?res=FB0610F7385E1A7493C6A9178FD85F438684F9 |title=New-Jersey Towns Growing Up at the Expense of New-York. - View Article - NYTimes.com |access-date=2014-03-30 |archive-date=2012-11-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121111045547/http://query.nytimes.com/mem/archive-free/pdf?res=FB0610F7385E1A7493C6A9178FD85F438684F9 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://query.nytimes.com/mem/archive-free/pdf?res=F20E13F8355414728DDDAD0A94DC405B808DF1D3 |title=NEW SUBURBAN ERA DAWNING IN JERSEY - Tunnels, Bridges, and Railroad Improvements Broadening the Commuting Area. - View Article - NYTimes.com |access-date=2014-03-30 |archive-date=2012-11-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121111023945/http://query.nytimes.com/mem/archive-free/pdf?res=F20E13F8355414728DDDAD0A94DC405B808DF1D3 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://query.nytimes.com/mem/archive-free/pdf?res=F40617F73C5D1A7493C0AB178FD85F468784F9 |title=THE NEW-JERSEY SUBURBS. - How New-York is Extending on the West Side of the Hudson-Some Interesting Facts as to the Growth of New-Jersey Near the City New-York. - View Article... |access-date=2014-03-30 |archive-date=2014-03-13 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140313182645/http://query.nytimes.com/mem/archive-free/pdf?res=F40617F73C5D1A7493C0AB178FD85F468784F9 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://query.nytimes.com/mem/archive-free/pdf?res=F10614FD3F5F1A7493C5A9178DD85F408784F9 |title=The Favorable Locations Described. - Jersey City And Environs. Elizabeth. Linden. Plainfield. Route Of The New-Jersey Railroad. On The Morris And Essex Railroad. On The Erie R... |access-date=2014-03-30 |archive-date=2012-11-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121111044731/http://query.nytimes.com/mem/archive-free/pdf?res=F10614FD3F5F1A7493C5A9178DD85F408784F9 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。历史上许多移民进入美国的门户[[埃利斯岛|埃利斯岛]]也位于该区，其中许多人选择留在该地区，使之成为全美国种族最多样化的地方之一。这里可能也是社会经济最多样化的地方，有全州最大的贫困区和最独特的郊区<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.time.com/time/magazine/article/0,9171,975561-5,00.html |title=存档副本 |accessdate=2011-01-27 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5wDkeTGqw?url=http://www.time.com/time/magazine/article/0,9171,975561-5,00.html |archivedate=2011-02-03 }}  </ref>。

